content: I've revised the Input section to include line numbers and specify the variable type just now. I've also revised the stub generator so that the order of the variables is consistent.
I changed it to medium, usually I ask for a consensus to make such change but really here it took me 10min with the most basic backtracking algorithm, and i see others think it should be medium too.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Initially, I thought "maybe this should be Medium".  That thought was several hours ago.
Getting a "green result" in the first few test cases happened quickly; for me it was well under an hour.  However, there are a few headaches to finishing the harder test cases.
This puzzle is simple yet requires the coder to apply some consideration to the solution or it will time out on harder test cases.  Very nice!

This problem felt more like a "Medium Difficulty" puzzle because it can still be done by brute force, no need to optimize data structures (like bitboards), and simple DFS with constraint checks   gets a result, and there wasn't anything I had to learn or lookup specifically for this challenge.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: This wasn't too difficult to accomplish with brute force.  It took about 2 hours and completed it in TypeScript.   Let me know if you want to see my solution.  I recommend changing the difficulty rating to "Medium"

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It is simplified puzzle of https://www.codingame.com/training/medium/3n-tiling or https://www.codingame.com/training/hard/dumbbells-solver
So, it is great for learning this concept before trying harder puzzles
